- Notify the player when a decayable item expires (e.g. "The rusty key crumbles to dust.")
- Remove StatSections from CharacterInstance and format everything from Actor and perks
- the wear command should have a config option to limit the slots it can apply to and then we can implement wield and hold properly.
- ActorRef.CharId checks (CharId != "") could use actor.IsCharacter() instead.
- OnDeath in CharacterInstance (character.go) heals the player to full HP before ending the
  session. This means the player sees a full HP prompt right before being disconnected, which
  looks wrong. Decide on a proper death/respawn policy (e.g. respawn at 1 HP, or defer the
  heal until login) and update the test in character_test.go to match.
## Light and Darkness
Current implementation: rooms grant `dark` perk to occupants. Two counters:
- `infravision` — personal grant (race, spell, item). Only the holder can see.
- `light` — equipment grant. Look handler scans all actors in the room; if anyone has it, darkness is negated for everyone.

Only affects the look handler today. Still needed:
- Darkness affecting target resolution beyond look (combat targeting, get, etc.)
- Light source objects with finite duration (burn time)
- Intrinsic-light objects (glowing crystal on the ground lights the room without being equipped) — would need an object flag or a room-level perk from the object
- Utility "light" spell: non-combat spell that adds a timed `light` grant to the room's PerkCache (e.g. 2 ticks). Uses existing timed-perk infrastructure. Requires distinguishing combat vs utility abilities so utility spells can auto-cast outside of combat.

